remarks.para:
For example, given the following OTPL definitions:


FlowB # defined in Module 'ModuleB'
{
    FlowItem Item2 TestX
}

FlowA # defined in Module 'ModuleA'
{
   FlowItem Item1 ModuleB::FlowB
}

MainFlow = ModuleA::FlowA


If this property is read during an execution of 'ModuleB::TestX' triggered via 'MainFlow', the
list returned will have the value
["MainFlow::ModuleA::FlowA", "ModuleA::FlowA::Item1", "ModuleB::FlowB::Item2"]
